<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="185" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,151,248]" pageId="8" pageNumber="185">
<taxonomicName box="[151,413,152,176]" class="Ostracoda" family="Xestoleberididae" genus="Xestoleberis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="8" pageNumber="185" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="umbonata">
<emphasis box="[151,413,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="185">Xestoleberis umbonata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was first recorded in Recent sediments of 
<collectingCountry box="[925,1037,151,176]" name="Argentina" pageId="8" pageNumber="185">Argentina</collectingCountry>
by 
<bibRefCitation box="[1087,1344,151,176]" pageId="8" pageNumber="185" refString="Whatley, R. C., Moguilevsky, A., Chadwick, J., Toy, N. &amp; Ramos, M. I. F. (1998) Ostracoda from the South West Atlantic. Part III: the Argentinian, Uruguayan and Southern Brazilian Continental Shelf. Revista Espanola de Micropaleontologia, 30, 89 - 116." type="journal article">
Whatley 
<emphasis box="[1193,1254,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="185">et al.</emphasis>
(
<number box="[1274,1335,152,176]" pageId="8" pageNumber="185" value="1998.0">1998</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. Ramos (
<number box="[159,217,188,212]" pageId="8" pageNumber="185" value="1998.0">1998</number>
) also recorded this species in the Southern region of 
<collectingCountry box="[851,922,188,213]" name="Brazil" pageId="8" pageNumber="185">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, where it was quite abundant. According to 
<bibRefCitation box="[151,402,223,248]" pageId="8" pageNumber="185" refString="Machado, C. P., Coimbra, J. C. &amp; Carreno, A. L. (2005) The ecological and zoogeographical significance of the sub-recent Ostracoda off Cabo Frio, Rio de Janeiro State, Brazil. Marine Micropaleontology, 55, 235 - 253. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1016 / j. marmicro. 2005.03.002" type="journal article">
Machado 
<emphasis box="[262,310,224,248]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="185">et al</emphasis>
. (
<number box="[333,394,223,248]" pageId="8" pageNumber="185" value="2005.0">2005</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[413,556,224,248]" class="Ostracoda" family="Xestoleberididae" genus="Xestoleberis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="8" pageNumber="185" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="umbonata">
<emphasis box="[413,430,225,248]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="185">X</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[444,556,224,248]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="185">umbonata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is one of the dominant marine ostracod species off the Cabo Frio area.
</paragraph>
